Class ExpectedResult

  • java.lang.Object
    • test.ExpectedResult

  • public final class ExpectedResult
extends java.lang.Object
    Represents an expected result of a test. This class is mainly useful to be able to check multiple lines of output with different criteria.

    Example:
    Say we expect some lines to be three times "Success!", an empty line afterwards, and then a line starting with "Error,". We would construct this Array:
    <pre> ExpectedResult[] expectedResults = new ExpectedResult[] { new ExpectedResult("Success!", TestType.SAME), new ExpectedResult("Success!", TestType.SAME), new ExpectedResult("Success!", TestType.SAME), new ExpectedResult(System.lineSeparator(), TestType.SAME), new ExpectedResult("Error,", TestType.STARTS_WITH) } </pre>
    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    Joshua Gleitze
    See Also:
    InteractiveConsoleTest.multiLineTest(String, ExpectedResult[], String...)
